WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.916 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.916 --> 00:00:07.395 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:07.395 --> 00:00:27.624 align:middle line:90%


00:00:27.624 --> 00:00:29.540 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: You've
all heard of "Joseph

00:00:29.540 --> 00:00:31.520 align:middle line:10%
and His Technicolor Dreamcoat."

00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:34.170 align:middle line:10%
Joseph's gift was
the gift of dreaming.

00:00:34.170 --> 00:00:36.020 align:middle line:84%
The gift we're going
to share with you today

00:00:36.020 --> 00:00:37.770 align:middle line:90%
was also the gift of dreaming.

00:00:37.770 --> 00:00:40.570 align:middle line:84%
You, too, have a technicolor
dreamcoat that Connie Kaplan

00:00:40.570 --> 00:00:42.570 align:middle line:90%
calls your invisible garment.

00:00:42.570 --> 00:00:45.520 align:middle line:84%
This beautiful method of
understanding self and soul

00:00:45.520 --> 00:00:48.340 align:middle line:84%
was brought forward when
Connie was spending nearly all

00:00:48.340 --> 00:00:52.514 align:middle line:84%
of her time sleeping, which
wasn't a good thing, right.

00:00:52.514 --> 00:00:53.430 align:middle line:90%
>>CONNIE KAPLAN: Well.

00:00:53.430 --> 00:00:54.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean,
it turned out--

00:00:54.310 --> 00:00:55.250 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: In
retrospect, it was fine.

00:00:55.250 --> 00:00:57.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, in
retrospect it was fine.

00:00:57.050 --> 00:00:59.710 align:middle line:84%
But it was a challenging
time in your life.

00:00:59.710 --> 00:01:02.780 align:middle line:84%
You weren't sleeping because
you wanted to necessarily.

00:01:02.780 --> 00:01:06.120 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about what was going
on in your life at that time.

00:01:06.120 --> 00:01:09.860 align:middle line:10%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, you know, I
was in my mid 30s, late 30s.

00:01:09.860 --> 00:01:14.590 align:middle line:10%
I had a great career, a great
marriage, wonderful child,

00:01:14.590 --> 00:01:16.692 align:middle line:10%
Saab convertible.

00:01:16.692 --> 00:01:17.775 align:middle line:90%
Everything was going well.

00:01:17.775 --> 00:01:18.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Living it large.

00:01:18.640 --> 00:01:19.440 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Uh huh.

00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:22.340 align:middle line:84%
Fast lane, working in
the television industry

00:01:22.340 --> 00:01:23.350 align:middle line:90%
in Los Angeles.

00:01:23.350 --> 00:01:25.740 align:middle line:90%
And one day, I woke up sick.

00:01:25.740 --> 00:01:27.840 align:middle line:84%
And I went to work
anyway because that's

00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:30.210 align:middle line:90%
what you do in television.

00:01:30.210 --> 00:01:32.532 align:middle line:84%
And by noon, I was just--
I wasn't functional.

00:01:32.532 --> 00:01:34.490 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they had to get
somebody drive me home.

00:01:34.490 --> 00:01:36.000 align:middle line:84%
So I thought, all right,
well, I've got the flu.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:37.480 align:middle line:90%
And that'll last for a while.

00:01:37.480 --> 00:01:43.470 align:middle line:84%
And then, well, I started on
the downward spiral, and I

00:01:43.470 --> 00:01:44.912 align:middle line:90%
just-- I lost my mind.

00:01:44.912 --> 00:01:46.120 align:middle line:90%
It's basically what happened.

00:01:46.120 --> 00:01:50.900 align:middle line:84%
Something was going on in my
brain, and I lost synapses,

00:01:50.900 --> 00:01:52.900 align:middle line:84%
you know, like, the
doorbell would ring

00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:55.980 align:middle line:84%
and I could not remember
what you were supposed to do.

00:01:55.980 --> 00:01:58.110 align:middle line:84%
Or the phone would ring,
and I could not figure out

00:01:58.110 --> 00:01:59.310 align:middle line:90%
how to get it to stop.

00:01:59.310 --> 00:02:03.526 align:middle line:84%
It was just-- I lost all
kinds of basic, you know--

00:02:03.526 --> 00:02:04.650 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Cognitive skills.

00:02:04.650 --> 00:02:06.300 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Cognitive
skills, yeah.

00:02:06.300 --> 00:02:11.740 align:middle line:84%
Um, and I just could
not stay awake,

00:02:11.740 --> 00:02:13.247 align:middle line:90%
just could not stay awake.

00:02:13.247 --> 00:02:15.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What happened--
what did you have?

00:02:15.080 --> 00:02:17.410 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Well, it was
not ever really diagnosed,

00:02:17.410 --> 00:02:22.640 align:middle line:84%
other than there was a
viral infection in my brain.

00:02:22.640 --> 00:02:26.070 align:middle line:84%
And that was during the
time-- that was, like,

00:02:26.070 --> 00:02:30.760 align:middle line:84%
pretty on the early end of all
those immune deficiency things,

00:02:30.760 --> 00:02:31.561 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:02:31.561 --> 00:02:32.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:02:32.360 --> 00:02:33.830 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Ep--
Epstein-Barr and--

00:02:33.830 --> 00:02:34.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Chronic
Fatigue Syndrome.

00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:35.500 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Chronic Fatigue, yeah.

00:02:35.500 --> 00:02:36.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And all that.

00:02:36.280 --> 00:02:37.080 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Right.

00:02:37.080 --> 00:02:41.200 align:middle line:84%
And all of those were basically
blamed on the patient,

00:02:41.200 --> 00:02:42.000 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:44.090 align:middle line:84%
It's your fault. There's
something wrong with you.

00:02:44.090 --> 00:02:45.631 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which
they've since learned

00:02:45.631 --> 00:02:48.370 align:middle line:84%
it's an auto immune deficiency,
oftentimes virally inspired.

00:02:48.370 --> 00:02:49.170 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah.

00:02:49.170 --> 00:02:49.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:02:49.970 --> 00:02:52.780 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: So many years later,
I finally got a diagnosis

00:02:52.780 --> 00:02:54.700 align:middle line:84%
that it was a viral
infection in the brain.

00:02:54.700 --> 00:02:57.410 align:middle line:84%
But at the time,
you know, thousands

00:02:57.410 --> 00:02:59.160 align:middle line:84%
of tests, it seemed--
thousands of dollars

00:02:59.160 --> 00:03:01.650 align:middle line:84%
worth of tests, at least,
couldn't find anything wrong

00:03:01.650 --> 00:03:02.480 align:middle line:90%
with me.

00:03:02.480 --> 00:03:07.029 align:middle line:84%
So, um, the doctor finally
just said to my husband, look,

00:03:07.029 --> 00:03:08.570 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
it is, but it's not

00:03:08.570 --> 00:03:11.260 align:middle line:84%
going to kill her so
just let her sleep.

00:03:11.260 --> 00:03:12.060 align:middle line:90%
So I did.

00:03:12.060 --> 00:03:15.850 align:middle line:84%
I slept probably like
15, 18 hours a day

00:03:15.850 --> 00:03:18.390 align:middle line:90%
for a couple of years.

00:03:18.390 --> 00:03:20.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I have a
question at this point.

00:03:20.140 --> 00:03:20.940 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Hm mm.

00:03:20.940 --> 00:03:22.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:03:22.010 --> 00:03:24.980 align:middle line:84%
We're going to be talking
about the soul in this,

00:03:24.980 --> 00:03:29.890 align:middle line:84%
and do-- this-- do you feel
in hindsight that this was

00:03:29.890 --> 00:03:32.980 align:middle line:84%
divinely orchestrated so you
could be out of your mind

00:03:32.980 --> 00:03:34.570 align:middle line:84%
and set your mind
aside for a while.

00:03:34.570 --> 00:03:37.570 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Say-- I'm not
going to say that because I

00:03:37.570 --> 00:03:41.160 align:middle line:84%
have such an aversion to the
blame the victim mentality

00:03:41.160 --> 00:03:42.060 align:middle line:90%
thing.

00:03:42.060 --> 00:03:45.850 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to say,
you know, the disease was

00:03:45.850 --> 00:03:47.826 align:middle line:90%
caused by something.

00:03:47.826 --> 00:03:50.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, I mean, do you
think it was a perfect time,

00:03:50.200 --> 00:03:52.900 align:middle line:84%
like a perfect storm, so you
could set your mind aside?

00:03:52.900 --> 00:03:54.810 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, I think that--
I think I had to go offline.

00:03:54.810 --> 00:03:56.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, exactly,
that's what I'm saying.

00:03:56.200 --> 00:03:57.000 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Right.

00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:57.930 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:03:57.930 --> 00:03:59.950 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: So I was
definitely offline.

00:03:59.950 --> 00:04:01.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Offline.

00:04:01.580 --> 00:04:04.600 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: And so the first thing
that happened after I finally

00:04:04.600 --> 00:04:07.240 align:middle line:84%
woke up a little bit
was that I started

00:04:07.240 --> 00:04:12.730 align:middle line:84%
realizing that I had
learned a lot about dreaming

00:04:12.730 --> 00:04:13.760 align:middle line:90%
in the dream.

00:04:13.760 --> 00:04:17.450 align:middle line:84%
While I was asleep, teachers
had come to me again and again

00:04:17.450 --> 00:04:20.550 align:middle line:84%
and again in, you
know, dreams that would

00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:22.310 align:middle line:90%
come over and over and over.

00:04:22.310 --> 00:04:27.720 align:middle line:84%
So that was the first sort of
mystical experience that I had.

00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:30.160 align:middle line:84%
And I immediately
started teaching

00:04:30.160 --> 00:04:33.699 align:middle line:84%
what I had learned about
dreaming at that time.

00:04:33.699 --> 00:04:35.990 align:middle line:84%
But that's not what we're
here to talk about today so--

00:04:35.990 --> 00:04:36.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:04:36.980 --> 00:04:42.430 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about what started
being-- coming through you,

00:04:42.430 --> 00:04:46.130 align:middle line:84%
and how your brain
started assembling it.

00:04:46.130 --> 00:04:51.100 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah, I just--
I would look at my dreams.

00:04:51.100 --> 00:04:55.440 align:middle line:84%
And for example, there
was this one woman

00:04:55.440 --> 00:04:58.620 align:middle line:84%
that would show up in
my dreams fairly often.

00:04:58.620 --> 00:05:02.400 align:middle line:84%
And she would gather a
group of women together.

00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:04.410 align:middle line:84%
And she would take
us into a cave.

00:05:04.410 --> 00:05:07.170 align:middle line:84%
And she would have us
reproduce the drawings that

00:05:07.170 --> 00:05:09.740 align:middle line:84%
were on the walls of
the cave as if we were

00:05:09.740 --> 00:05:11.500 align:middle line:84%
in one of those caves
in France, you know,

00:05:11.500 --> 00:05:13.124 align:middle line:84%
where all those
wonderful drawings are.

00:05:13.124 --> 00:05:15.090 align:middle line:84%
We would reproduce
them in some way.

00:05:15.090 --> 00:05:17.970 align:middle line:84%
And then, if she was pleased
with what we were doing,

00:05:17.970 --> 00:05:19.720 align:middle line:90%
we could take a nap.

00:05:19.720 --> 00:05:21.820 align:middle line:84%
So you get to take
a nap in a dream.

00:05:21.820 --> 00:05:23.830 align:middle line:84%
That's like a very
special thing.

00:05:23.830 --> 00:05:25.640 align:middle line:84%
And then, she would--
as we went to sleep,

00:05:25.640 --> 00:05:30.690 align:middle line:84%
she would point out the
wall-- the door of the cave,

00:05:30.690 --> 00:05:34.460 align:middle line:84%
and there would
be the full moon.

00:05:34.460 --> 00:05:36.890 align:middle line:84%
Now, I didn't realize it
while this was going on,

00:05:36.890 --> 00:05:41.030 align:middle line:84%
because I didn't connect hardly
any dots while it was going on.

00:05:41.030 --> 00:05:44.260 align:middle line:84%
But a couple years
later, I realized

00:05:44.260 --> 00:05:47.040 align:middle line:84%
she was telling us
something about the moon.

00:05:47.040 --> 00:05:50.770 align:middle line:84%
And so I looked up
on a lunar calendar

00:05:50.770 --> 00:05:52.530 align:middle line:90%
when I had those dreams.

00:05:52.530 --> 00:05:54.870 align:middle line:84%
So this woman had
come in a dream

00:05:54.870 --> 00:05:58.430 align:middle line:84%
every full moon for
13 straight months.

00:05:58.430 --> 00:06:01.734 align:middle line:84%
So I started realizing,
all right, we

00:06:01.734 --> 00:06:03.150 align:middle line:84%
need to start
looking at the lunar

00:06:03.150 --> 00:06:06.330 align:middle line:84%
influences on our dreaming, you
know, so that kind of thing.

00:06:06.330 --> 00:06:09.580 align:middle line:84%
It was just like kind of
connecting the dots in a very

00:06:09.580 --> 00:06:12.570 align:middle line:90%
nontraditional way.

00:06:12.570 --> 00:06:15.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Then,
at some point, you

00:06:15.490 --> 00:06:18.600 align:middle line:84%
started getting a body
of information that

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:19.760 align:middle line:90%
took a while to assimilate.

00:06:19.760 --> 00:06:20.560 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Right.

00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:21.935 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
again, I think it's

00:06:21.935 --> 00:06:24.540 align:middle line:84%
important to point out that
you were into your Saab,

00:06:24.540 --> 00:06:26.580 align:middle line:84%
you know, your life,
your family, your work.

00:06:26.580 --> 00:06:30.170 align:middle line:84%
You were not particularly prone
toward metaphysical thought

00:06:30.170 --> 00:06:31.270 align:middle line:90%
or contemplation.

00:06:31.270 --> 00:06:32.070 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Exactly.

00:06:32.070 --> 00:06:34.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this is all coming
out of seemingly nowhere.

00:06:34.820 --> 00:06:35.620 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Right.

00:06:35.620 --> 00:06:37.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's
talk about that.

00:06:37.350 --> 00:06:39.058 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: So I do have
to start by saying

00:06:39.058 --> 00:06:40.490 align:middle line:90%
my father was a minister.

00:06:40.490 --> 00:06:45.630 align:middle line:84%
So I did grow up in a household
where at least religion,

00:06:45.630 --> 00:06:49.130 align:middle line:84%
and to a certain extent also
spirituality, was, you know,

00:06:49.130 --> 00:06:50.920 align:middle line:90%
dominant.

00:06:50.920 --> 00:06:52.850 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I'd been
churched half to death

00:06:52.850 --> 00:06:54.058 align:middle line:90%
by the time I got to college.

00:06:54.058 --> 00:06:57.020 align:middle line:84%
So, you know, out of the
house, I kind of went wild.

00:06:57.020 --> 00:06:59.520 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't really
participate in any kind

00:06:59.520 --> 00:07:06.700 align:middle line:84%
of religious stuff between then
and when I was in my late 30s.

00:07:06.700 --> 00:07:10.290 align:middle line:84%
Um, so no, I was not in
the practice of any kind

00:07:10.290 --> 00:07:14.720 align:middle line:90%
of spiritual work really.

00:07:14.720 --> 00:07:17.060 align:middle line:84%
So now, it's a few
years after I've

00:07:17.060 --> 00:07:21.030 align:middle line:84%
been teaching this dreaming
work, and my father is dying.

00:07:21.030 --> 00:07:24.170 align:middle line:84%
And so my sisters and I
go home to be with him

00:07:24.170 --> 00:07:26.630 align:middle line:90%
during his last days.

00:07:26.630 --> 00:07:31.810 align:middle line:84%
And it turned out that I was
actually in the room with him

00:07:31.810 --> 00:07:33.880 align:middle line:90%
in his last few hours.

00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:37.390 align:middle line:84%
And I was sitting by his bed
and holding his hand and kind

00:07:37.390 --> 00:07:41.410 align:middle line:84%
of, you know, for a girl
who doesn't pray, praying,

00:07:41.410 --> 00:07:44.680 align:middle line:84%
you know, and just kind of
saying, look, he's ready to go.

00:07:44.680 --> 00:07:47.700 align:middle line:84%
Why keep pumping these lungs
and pumping this heart?

00:07:47.700 --> 00:07:49.930 align:middle line:90%
He's, you know, it's done.

00:07:49.930 --> 00:07:51.430 align:middle line:84%
And I heard the
door open behind me.

00:07:51.430 --> 00:07:53.290 align:middle line:84%
But this was, like,
just prior to dawn

00:07:53.290 --> 00:07:55.695 align:middle line:84%
so I knew it wasn't
visitors coming in.

00:07:55.695 --> 00:07:58.070 align:middle line:84%
So I thought it must have been
a nurse coming in to check

00:07:58.070 --> 00:07:59.280 align:middle line:90%
his vitals or something.

00:07:59.280 --> 00:08:01.080 align:middle line:90%
I stood up and turned around.

00:08:01.080 --> 00:08:05.230 align:middle line:84%
And there were two
angels in the room,

00:08:05.230 --> 00:08:10.330 align:middle line:84%
big, tall, backlit,
dressed sort of like John

00:08:10.330 --> 00:08:11.650 align:middle line:90%
Travolta in "Michael."

00:08:11.650 --> 00:08:12.450 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:08:12.450 --> 00:08:13.250 align:middle line:90%


00:08:13.250 --> 00:08:15.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love that film.

00:08:15.660 --> 00:08:18.350 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: And I knew they were
angels because of the sense

00:08:18.350 --> 00:08:19.910 align:middle line:90%
of love in the room.

00:08:19.910 --> 00:08:23.960 align:middle line:84%
It was just an
overwhelming sense of love.

00:08:23.960 --> 00:08:26.680 align:middle line:84%
And Regina, I was in
one of those moments

00:08:26.680 --> 00:08:30.250 align:middle line:84%
where you-- I didn't
believe in angels, right.

00:08:30.250 --> 00:08:31.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:08:31.050 --> 00:08:34.570 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: So you've either got
to go with your experience,

00:08:34.570 --> 00:08:38.220 align:middle line:84%
and experience something that
you don't believe can happen.

00:08:38.220 --> 00:08:40.140 align:middle line:84%
Or you've got to cut
the experience off

00:08:40.140 --> 00:08:42.820 align:middle line:84%
so you can be faithful
to your belief system.

00:08:42.820 --> 00:08:45.150 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, most
people stay faithful

00:08:45.150 --> 00:08:46.420 align:middle line:90%
to their belief system.

00:08:46.420 --> 00:08:48.424 align:middle line:84%
But in that moment,
I was kind of too--

00:08:48.424 --> 00:08:49.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
you're vulnerable.

00:08:49.840 --> 00:08:51.020 align:middle line:90%
Your father's passing.

00:08:51.020 --> 00:08:52.550 align:middle line:90%
You're very vulnerable and open.

00:08:52.550 --> 00:08:53.650 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah.

00:08:53.650 --> 00:08:55.885 align:middle line:84%
So I kind of decided to
go with the experience

00:08:55.885 --> 00:08:56.685 align:middle line:90%
in that nanosecond.

00:08:56.685 --> 00:09:02.110 align:middle line:84%
And-- and, um, but still I was
kind of sarcastic and whatever.

00:09:02.110 --> 00:09:05.360 align:middle line:84%
And I said, why'd
you use the door.

00:09:05.360 --> 00:09:06.160 align:middle line:90%
And they go--

00:09:06.160 --> 00:09:07.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Angels
don't need doors.

00:09:07.020 --> 00:09:08.353 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: You don't need a door.

00:09:08.353 --> 00:09:10.880 align:middle line:84%
And they said, we're here
to open all the portals.

00:09:10.880 --> 00:09:13.160 align:middle line:90%
And I kind of went, whoa.

00:09:13.160 --> 00:09:15.890 align:middle line:84%
So they talked to me
for a little while.

00:09:15.890 --> 00:09:17.740 align:middle line:84%
And they said, there's
a body of information

00:09:17.740 --> 00:09:19.490 align:middle line:90%
that we need written down.

00:09:19.490 --> 00:09:23.540 align:middle line:84%
There are things
that most people

00:09:23.540 --> 00:09:28.190 align:middle line:84%
are misunderstanding about
what the human incarnation is.

00:09:28.190 --> 00:09:30.850 align:middle line:84%
And those corrections--
those misunderstandings

00:09:30.850 --> 00:09:34.240 align:middle line:84%
need to be corrected
if the human species is

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:35.990 align:middle line:90%
going to evolve.

00:09:35.990 --> 00:09:39.450 align:middle line:84%
And it's OK if you
don't want to evolve.

00:09:39.450 --> 00:09:42.780 align:middle line:84%
But if you're going to
evolve, a few changes

00:09:42.780 --> 00:09:46.110 align:middle line:84%
need to be made in your
understanding of why

00:09:46.110 --> 00:09:47.740 align:middle line:90%
you are embodied.

00:09:47.740 --> 00:09:50.230 align:middle line:84%
So we need you to
write this down.

00:09:50.230 --> 00:09:55.840 align:middle line:84%
Well, I was not in the
mood to become, like,

00:09:55.840 --> 00:09:58.670 align:middle line:84%
one of those people that sits on
a stage and goes into a trance

00:09:58.670 --> 00:10:02.770 align:middle line:84%
and starts-- you know, I
just, that-- I-- that wasn't

00:10:02.770 --> 00:10:04.730 align:middle line:90%
my world.

00:10:04.730 --> 00:10:08.915 align:middle line:84%
So I said, yeah, no, I don't-- I
could refer you to some people.

00:10:08.915 --> 00:10:09.785 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:10:09.785 --> 00:10:09.834 align:middle line:90%


00:10:09.834 --> 00:10:11.250 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: And they
just said, uh--

00:10:11.250 --> 00:10:11.670 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's funny.

00:10:11.670 --> 00:10:13.545 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: They laughed,
and they said, do you

00:10:13.545 --> 00:10:16.050 align:middle line:84%
know who you're talking
to, negotiating here

00:10:16.050 --> 00:10:18.150 align:middle line:84%
with the angels of death
or something, right.

00:10:18.150 --> 00:10:21.890 align:middle line:84%
So I said, OK, eventually, I
said, OK, well, tell me more

00:10:21.890 --> 00:10:24.280 align:middle line:90%
about this body of information.

00:10:24.280 --> 00:10:29.220 align:middle line:84%
And so they just blasted
me or something happened.

00:10:29.220 --> 00:10:36.510 align:middle line:84%
And I suddenly found myself, my
consciousness in this dimension

00:10:36.510 --> 00:10:41.110 align:middle line:84%
that I can only describe
as sound, color, and form.

00:10:41.110 --> 00:10:46.410 align:middle line:84%
I was kind of walking through a
forest of neon geometric shapes

00:10:46.410 --> 00:10:50.540 align:middle line:84%
and hearing tones
coming out of the colors

00:10:50.540 --> 00:10:59.200 align:middle line:84%
and, um-- yeah, it was just
this amazing experience.

00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:00.960 align:middle line:84%
I knew that I was
in the place where

00:11:00.960 --> 00:11:06.830 align:middle line:84%
all the answers are, which
some people would call God.

00:11:06.830 --> 00:11:09.490 align:middle line:84%
I knew that if I could
think of a question,

00:11:09.490 --> 00:11:10.865 align:middle line:84%
it would be answered
immediately.

00:11:10.865 --> 00:11:13.156 align:middle line:84%
But when you're in the place
where all the answers are,

00:11:13.156 --> 00:11:14.410 align:middle line:90%
there aren't any questions.

00:11:14.410 --> 00:11:18.470 align:middle line:84%
So it wasn't like I
could test or, you know,

00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:21.360 align:middle line:84%
learn anything there,
except everything

00:11:21.360 --> 00:11:24.620 align:middle line:84%
seemed to have been
downloaded in those about

00:11:24.620 --> 00:11:27.620 align:middle line:90%
45 minutes that I was there.

00:11:27.620 --> 00:11:30.020 align:middle line:84%
So I kind of came back
into the room eventually.

00:11:30.020 --> 00:11:32.545 align:middle line:84%
And I said, all right,
I'll write it down but--

00:11:32.545 --> 00:11:34.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you came back
with structural memory?

00:11:34.670 --> 00:11:35.980 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Uh huh.

00:11:35.980 --> 00:11:36.780 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:36.780 --> 00:11:37.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Of all of this?

00:11:37.020 --> 00:11:38.010 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:38.010 --> 00:11:39.801 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: It's kind of
like a lot of people

00:11:39.801 --> 00:11:43.140 align:middle line:84%
describe as an NDE, a
near-death experience,

00:11:43.140 --> 00:11:47.200 align:middle line:84%
where they actually go to the
other side and then come back.

00:11:47.200 --> 00:11:48.842 align:middle line:90%
But it wasn't my death.

00:11:48.842 --> 00:11:49.800 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, right.

00:11:49.800 --> 00:11:52.310 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: It was somebody
else's death but whatever.

00:11:52.310 --> 00:11:55.730 align:middle line:84%
It was-- it's-- I-- I sense
a familiarity when I talk

00:11:55.730 --> 00:11:58.110 align:middle line:84%
to people that have had
NDEs, with the experience.

00:11:58.110 --> 00:12:00.420 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, I said,
I'll write it down,

00:12:00.420 --> 00:12:04.434 align:middle line:84%
but I'm not going
to tell anybody.

00:12:04.434 --> 00:12:05.430 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:12:05.430 --> 00:12:05.930 align:middle line:90%


00:12:05.930 --> 00:12:06.730 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Right.

00:12:06.730 --> 00:12:09.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I mean,
thus, here you are now.

00:12:09.370 --> 00:12:10.170 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah.

00:12:10.170 --> 00:12:12.891 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You have not exactly
been promoting your work.

00:12:12.891 --> 00:12:13.890 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: No, I haven't.

00:12:13.890 --> 00:12:14.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:12:14.540 --> 00:12:15.373 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: I haven't.

00:12:15.373 --> 00:12:18.960 align:middle line:84%
But that's-- they said
to me, you write it down.

00:12:18.960 --> 00:12:22.210 align:middle line:84%
We'll send you the people
that need to know it.

00:12:22.210 --> 00:12:24.190 align:middle line:84%
And so we'll take care
of that side of it.

00:12:24.190 --> 00:12:25.119 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:12:25.119 --> 00:12:26.035 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Here we are.

00:12:26.035 --> 00:12:26.993 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Here you are.

00:12:26.993 --> 00:12:28.040 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, exactly.

00:12:28.040 --> 00:12:30.600 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
the body of knowledge.

00:12:30.600 --> 00:12:32.800 align:middle line:84%
Before we even get into
the body of knowledge,

00:12:32.800 --> 00:12:36.270 align:middle line:84%
this whole notion that
we're unclear on the point

00:12:36.270 --> 00:12:38.510 align:middle line:84%
of our incarnations
on the planet.

00:12:38.510 --> 00:12:40.190 align:middle line:90%
Let's start there.

00:12:40.190 --> 00:12:41.440 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: OK.

00:12:41.440 --> 00:12:44.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So they
said, well, let

00:12:44.970 --> 00:12:48.330 align:middle line:84%
me just say that over the
next three or four months

00:12:48.330 --> 00:12:49.762 align:middle line:84%
was when this body
of information

00:12:49.762 --> 00:12:50.720 align:middle line:90%
started coming through.

00:12:50.720 --> 00:12:52.570 align:middle line:84%
I would get up in the
middle of the night

00:12:52.570 --> 00:12:53.930 align:middle line:90%
and do a little writing.

00:12:53.930 --> 00:12:56.270 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't like trance writing
or anything like that.

00:12:56.270 --> 00:12:57.830 align:middle line:84%
It was just, I
knew what to write

00:12:57.830 --> 00:12:59.895 align:middle line:84%
down at 3 o'clock in
the morning, right.

00:12:59.895 --> 00:13:00.695 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:13:00.695 --> 00:13:03.080 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: And so over
the next few months,

00:13:03.080 --> 00:13:06.100 align:middle line:84%
this body of information
had come through.

00:13:06.100 --> 00:13:08.390 align:middle line:84%
And one of the most
important parts of it

00:13:08.390 --> 00:13:11.650 align:middle line:84%
is most people think
that you're here

00:13:11.650 --> 00:13:19.920 align:middle line:84%
to do something, accomplish
something, uh, you know,

00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:21.700 align:middle line:84%
put something out
into the world,

00:13:21.700 --> 00:13:24.730 align:middle line:90%
and get money back for it.

00:13:24.730 --> 00:13:27.450 align:middle line:84%
Or some people-- most people--
most people-- a lot of people

00:13:27.450 --> 00:13:31.030 align:middle line:84%
think you're here
to learn lessons.

00:13:31.030 --> 00:13:32.900 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
here think you're here

00:13:32.900 --> 00:13:36.640 align:middle line:84%
to do something with karma, burn
off karma or create karma or do

00:13:36.640 --> 00:13:40.930 align:middle line:84%
something with that
reciprocity kind of energy.

00:13:40.930 --> 00:13:43.140 align:middle line:84%
And they said, no,
it's none of that.

00:13:43.140 --> 00:13:47.150 align:middle line:90%
You are here to deliver a gift.

00:13:47.150 --> 00:13:49.820 align:middle line:84%
That's all you're here to
do is to deliver the gift.

00:13:49.820 --> 00:13:54.370 align:middle line:84%
And the way you deliver
the gift is to be the gift.

00:13:54.370 --> 00:13:57.960 align:middle line:84%
The gift comes from
the level of soul.

00:13:57.960 --> 00:14:00.630 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't come
from your willfulness.

00:14:00.630 --> 00:14:05.270 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't come from your
mental, rational mind.

00:14:05.270 --> 00:14:09.680 align:middle line:84%
It is a gift from soul that
wants to be embodied in form.

00:14:09.680 --> 00:14:13.410 align:middle line:84%
And all you have
to do is give it.

00:14:13.410 --> 00:14:15.880 align:middle line:90%
So that's kind of radical.

00:14:15.880 --> 00:14:22.000 align:middle line:84%
And it-- you know, they
emphasize that being the gift

00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:26.540 align:middle line:84%
rather than doing anything is
your reason for incarnating.

00:14:26.540 --> 00:14:27.341 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Hm mm.

00:14:27.341 --> 00:14:29.423 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: So whenever I
tell people that, they go,

00:14:29.423 --> 00:14:30.580 align:middle line:90%
oh my god, I can't do that.

00:14:30.580 --> 00:14:33.139 align:middle line:84%
Because if I just be, then
I'll just sit on the couch,

00:14:33.139 --> 00:14:35.430 align:middle line:84%
and I'll never do anything,
and then, I'll be homeless.

00:14:35.430 --> 00:14:37.096 align:middle line:84%
And I'll walk around
with all my clothes

00:14:37.096 --> 00:14:40.310 align:middle line:84%
in a-- you know,
in a grocery cart.

00:14:40.310 --> 00:14:41.380 align:middle line:90%
And I'll have bad hair.

00:14:41.380 --> 00:14:42.180 align:middle line:90%
I can't do that.

00:14:42.180 --> 00:14:42.585 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, right.

00:14:42.585 --> 00:14:43.360 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: That's terrible.

00:14:43.360 --> 00:14:45.401 align:middle line:84%
I won't have any money,
and I'll starve to death.

00:14:45.401 --> 00:14:46.910 align:middle line:90%
It's not that at all.

00:14:46.910 --> 00:14:47.810 align:middle line:90%
It's not that at all.

00:14:47.810 --> 00:14:53.450 align:middle line:84%
It's that if you learn to
be the gift that you are,

00:14:53.450 --> 00:14:58.430 align:middle line:84%
you're doingness shows up in
front of you and says do me.

00:14:58.430 --> 00:15:02.110 align:middle line:84%
And it's something that
is authentically yours

00:15:02.110 --> 00:15:06.276 align:middle line:84%
to do rather than
your having to make up

00:15:06.276 --> 00:15:07.400 align:middle line:90%
what you're supposed to do.

00:15:07.400 --> 00:15:09.066 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it
doesn't mean that there

00:15:09.066 --> 00:15:11.730 align:middle line:84%
aren't some basic things or
skills or things you need

00:15:11.730 --> 00:15:13.710 align:middle line:84%
to learn along the way
within the incarnation

00:15:13.710 --> 00:15:16.090 align:middle line:90%
so you are able to express this.

00:15:16.090 --> 00:15:17.960 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Exactly,
because what-- you know,

00:15:17.960 --> 00:15:20.120 align:middle line:84%
when you take an
incarnation as a human,

00:15:20.120 --> 00:15:24.140 align:middle line:84%
then you have to
appear to be a human.

00:15:24.140 --> 00:15:26.690 align:middle line:84%
So you have this, you
have a mental body

00:15:26.690 --> 00:15:28.750 align:middle line:84%
and an emotional body
and a physical body

00:15:28.750 --> 00:15:30.270 align:middle line:90%
and an ethical body.

00:15:30.270 --> 00:15:32.710 align:middle line:84%
And all of those bodies
have to work together

00:15:32.710 --> 00:15:37.760 align:middle line:84%
to create this personality
through which the gift can

00:15:37.760 --> 00:15:39.040 align:middle line:90%
be delivered.

00:15:39.040 --> 00:15:43.070 align:middle line:84%
So those bodies are combined
in the-- most people

00:15:43.070 --> 00:15:45.250 align:middle line:84%
would call those the
ego, the ego body.

00:15:45.250 --> 00:15:48.670 align:middle line:90%


00:15:48.670 --> 00:15:50.620 align:middle line:90%
That's where free will is.

00:15:50.620 --> 00:15:54.280 align:middle line:84%
And so that's where
you can make choices.

00:15:54.280 --> 00:15:58.160 align:middle line:84%
And too often, because
of socialization,

00:15:58.160 --> 00:16:00.810 align:middle line:84%
because of our
culturalization, we

00:16:00.810 --> 00:16:04.900 align:middle line:84%
make choices that are not in
our best interest, you know,

00:16:04.900 --> 00:16:09.780 align:middle line:84%
that are not coming from an
authentic space within us.

00:16:09.780 --> 00:16:13.820 align:middle line:84%
We make willful choices
that block our own gift

00:16:13.820 --> 00:16:15.870 align:middle line:90%
from being received.

00:16:15.870 --> 00:16:20.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: See now, this is the
rub in all of it for humanity,

00:16:20.150 --> 00:16:20.990 align:middle line:90%
in general.

00:16:20.990 --> 00:16:24.060 align:middle line:84%
And I guess that's why the body
of information came through

00:16:24.060 --> 00:16:27.590 align:middle line:84%
is to start learning how to open
these channels of communication

00:16:27.590 --> 00:16:31.060 align:middle line:84%
and start allowing yourselves
to express that unique thing

00:16:31.060 --> 00:16:32.830 align:middle line:90%
that we each offer.

00:16:32.830 --> 00:16:36.860 align:middle line:84%
But when a person--
and I want to-- I

00:16:36.860 --> 00:16:41.070 align:middle line:84%
want to get your impression
on how this works.

00:16:41.070 --> 00:16:45.220 align:middle line:84%
When a person feels, because
of societal conditioning,

00:16:45.220 --> 00:16:48.240 align:middle line:84%
unable to hear their
own voice, their

00:16:48.240 --> 00:16:51.020 align:middle line:84%
own higher voice,
whisper, whatever

00:16:51.020 --> 00:16:53.680 align:middle line:84%
you want to call that,
from the soul, you do.

00:16:53.680 --> 00:16:55.430 align:middle line:84%
You have a lot of
suffering on the planet.

00:16:55.430 --> 00:16:57.931 align:middle line:84%
You have people working
as automatons almost,

00:16:57.931 --> 00:16:59.430 align:middle line:84%
just kind of getting
through the day

00:16:59.430 --> 00:17:02.420 align:middle line:90%
to pay for the rent or whatnot.

00:17:02.420 --> 00:17:06.230 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about--
let's talk about that part

00:17:06.230 --> 00:17:10.119 align:middle line:84%
now before we go into the
rest of the system itself,

00:17:10.119 --> 00:17:13.390 align:middle line:84%
opening those means
of communication.

00:17:13.390 --> 00:17:17.190 align:middle line:84%
And then, the overlay of free
will once that's happened.

00:17:17.190 --> 00:17:26.040 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, um, it-- a lot
of it has to do with vocabulary

00:17:26.040 --> 00:17:30.000 align:middle line:84%
and how you ask
yourself the questions

00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:35.060 align:middle line:84%
about what-- about doingness,
about what you are to do.

00:17:35.060 --> 00:17:40.930 align:middle line:84%
When you look up your
principles and discover

00:17:40.930 --> 00:17:45.230 align:middle line:84%
what your invisible garment--
what your fiber-- the fiber

00:17:45.230 --> 00:17:49.310 align:middle line:84%
of your being is,
what you realize is,

00:17:49.310 --> 00:17:52.730 align:middle line:90%
I don't own these principles.

00:17:52.730 --> 00:17:57.530 align:middle line:84%
They are simply trying to
express through a personality.

00:17:57.530 --> 00:18:01.410 align:middle line:84%
So the real key is to
get out of the way.

00:18:01.410 --> 00:18:05.360 align:middle line:84%
So it's really about subtracting
rather than adding anything.

00:18:05.360 --> 00:18:09.330 align:middle line:84%
It's about learning how
to get out of the way

00:18:09.330 --> 00:18:15.250 align:middle line:84%
so that these principles can
just show up and call forth,

00:18:15.250 --> 00:18:18.029 align:middle line:84%
you know, magnetize what
your next doingness step is.

00:18:18.029 --> 00:18:19.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And for
most people, that's

00:18:19.570 --> 00:18:21.270 align:middle line:90%
very difficult because of fear.

00:18:21.270 --> 00:18:22.070 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Fear.

00:18:22.070 --> 00:18:24.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: All the things you
talked about right off the bat,

00:18:24.570 --> 00:18:26.526 align:middle line:90%
but A, the big F, the F word.

00:18:26.526 --> 00:18:27.650 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah, the F word.

00:18:27.650 --> 00:18:30.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The F word, and also
all these mental constructs

00:18:30.780 --> 00:18:33.764 align:middle line:84%
of what life is supposed to look
like as you also talked about

00:18:33.764 --> 00:18:34.680 align:middle line:90%
in the very beginning.

00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:36.440 align:middle line:84%
So you have a lot
of noise happening

00:18:36.440 --> 00:18:40.950 align:middle line:84%
from the conscious mind
and from the fear factor

00:18:40.950 --> 00:18:42.410 align:middle line:90%
from the amygdala.

00:18:42.410 --> 00:18:46.280 align:middle line:84%
And you have to-- you can't
hear yourself through that.

00:18:46.280 --> 00:18:49.670 align:middle line:84%
I mean, basically, one can't
hear oneself through that.

00:18:49.670 --> 00:18:52.620 align:middle line:84%
So do you have any-- I mean,
I have a couple of things

00:18:52.620 --> 00:18:53.930 align:middle line:90%
that I resonate with.

00:18:53.930 --> 00:18:56.020 align:middle line:84%
But what are some of the
things you resonate with?

00:18:56.020 --> 00:18:58.655 align:middle line:84%
And having a person
assist themself

00:18:58.655 --> 00:19:01.030 align:middle line:84%
in getting out of their own
way so they can actually hear

00:19:01.030 --> 00:19:02.940 align:middle line:90%
their voice, their true voice.

00:19:02.940 --> 00:19:05.330 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Well, one of the
things that you can do,

00:19:05.330 --> 00:19:08.610 align:middle line:84%
which I find very interesting
