00:20:10.860 --> 00:20:12.267 align:middle line:90%
when there's a bear behind me.

00:20:12.267 --> 00:20:13.067 align:middle line:90%
Otherwise--

00:20:13.067 --> 00:20:13.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:20:13.980 --> 00:20:14.780 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: You know.

00:20:14.780 --> 00:20:15.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're not--
we're not living that way.

00:20:15.890 --> 00:20:17.780 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: We're not going to
sit here and make up stuff

00:20:17.780 --> 00:20:18.826 align:middle line:90%
to be afraid of anymore.

00:20:18.826 --> 00:20:19.626 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:20:19.626 --> 00:20:20.672 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: So.

00:20:20.672 --> 00:20:22.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which is
essentially what

00:20:22.130 --> 00:20:23.870 align:middle line:84%
society does, which
essentially it's

00:20:23.870 --> 00:20:25.580 align:middle line:90%
programmed to do exactly that.

00:20:25.580 --> 00:20:26.960 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: What if, what
if, what if, what if.

00:20:26.960 --> 00:20:28.668 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because it
keeps you in a state

00:20:28.668 --> 00:20:33.460 align:middle line:84%
of neediness and dependency
on all systems and structures.

00:20:33.460 --> 00:20:36.910 align:middle line:84%
And so what you're talking about
is this a person breaking free

00:20:36.910 --> 00:20:40.390 align:middle line:84%
of all systems and
structures and fear itself.

00:20:40.390 --> 00:20:43.090 align:middle line:84%
And for me, I look at it
on a really simple level.

00:20:43.090 --> 00:20:45.230 align:middle line:84%
I remember when my
son was quite young,

00:20:45.230 --> 00:20:50.280 align:middle line:84%
teaching him to make
decisions under his own steam

00:20:50.280 --> 00:20:51.630 align:middle line:90%
when he was still young.

00:20:51.630 --> 00:20:53.950 align:middle line:84%
And I said, honey,
you can feel it.

00:20:53.950 --> 00:20:57.500 align:middle line:84%
You'll find a lifting or
a sinking in the stomach.

00:20:57.500 --> 00:20:59.640 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I always
explained it to him.

00:20:59.640 --> 00:21:02.250 align:middle line:84%
So when you're
contemplating something,

00:21:02.250 --> 00:21:04.150 align:middle line:84%
see how it's feeling
in your body.

00:21:04.150 --> 00:21:07.302 align:middle line:84%
And butterflies are not to
be confused with anxiety.

00:21:07.302 --> 00:21:08.885 align:middle line:84%
These are different
kinds of feelings.

00:21:08.885 --> 00:21:09.240 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, exactly.

00:21:09.240 --> 00:21:11.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You know, you
go through what they were.

00:21:11.610 --> 00:21:15.740 align:middle line:84%
And it really is a feeling
state to feel your way

00:21:15.740 --> 00:21:18.570 align:middle line:90%
to a little more openness.

00:21:18.570 --> 00:21:22.190 align:middle line:84%
And there are 1,000
techniques to do it.

