one thing I've always
felt guilty about

00:37:42.480 --> 00:37:44.630 align:middle line:84%
was very similar to what
you feel guilty about.

00:37:44.630 --> 00:37:48.170 align:middle line:84%
But it had to do during the
school years with my son.

00:37:48.170 --> 00:37:51.290 align:middle line:84%
And that was, you had your
uber-moms who were there.

00:37:51.290 --> 00:37:54.090 align:middle line:84%
And they were the ones that
volunteered for everything.

00:37:54.090 --> 00:37:55.940 align:middle line:84%
And they got awards at
the end of the year.

00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:57.850 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, there
was a lot of politics

00:37:57.850 --> 00:37:59.330 align:middle line:90%
involved in that little circle.

00:37:59.330 --> 00:38:00.330 align:middle line:90%
And I couldn't stand it.

00:38:00.330 --> 00:38:01.871 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to go
anywhere near it.

00:38:01.871 --> 00:38:03.160 align:middle line:90%
I never volunteered.

00:38:03.160 --> 00:38:06.400 align:middle line:84%
But when it was with
the kids, I volunteered.

00:38:06.400 --> 00:38:10.140 align:middle line:84%
As long as I was isolated with
the kids, to drive them places,

00:38:10.140 --> 00:38:14.050 align:middle line:84%
take them on camping
trips, and carpool.

00:38:14.050 --> 00:38:15.740 align:middle line:84%
And it was just me
and the kids, and we

00:38:15.740 --> 00:38:19.492 align:middle line:84%
could talk about fun things
together and explore and play.

00:38:19.492 --> 00:38:20.700 align:middle line:90%
I was totally cool with that.

00:38:20.700 --> 00:38:22.870 align:middle line:84%
I just couldn't deal
with that burden

00:38:22.870 --> 00:38:25.050 align:middle line:90%
of being with the parents.

00:38:25.050 --> 00:38:27.260 align:middle line:84%
And of course, the mothers
didn't care for me.

00:38:27.260 --> 00:38:30.050 align:middle line:84%
I was that weird
"out there" mother.

00:38:30.050 --> 00:38:30.960 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah, yeah.

00:38:30.960 --> 00:38:33.770 align:middle line:84%
Those are the kinds of things
that we experience in life,

00:38:33.770 --> 00:38:37.180 align:middle line:84%
that because we-- there
are so many should's.

00:38:37.180 --> 00:38:38.665 align:middle line:90%
There are just so many should's.

00:38:38.665 --> 00:38:38.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:38:38.870 --> 00:38:41.470 align:middle line:84%
So not everybody should be
volunteering all the time.

00:38:41.470 --> 00:38:41.785 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: No.

00:38:41.785 --> 00:38:42.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:38:42.100 --> 00:38:44.391 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: I mean, it's a
great thing for the people who

00:38:44.391 --> 00:38:45.470 align:middle line:90%
should be volunteering.

00:38:45.470 --> 00:38:45.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:38:45.700 --> 00:38:46.330 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: To volunteer.

00:38:46.330 --> 00:38:48.163 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now, where
are the volunteers?

00:38:48.163 --> 00:38:50.825 align:middle line:84%
Are they containment, ascending,
containment, descending,

00:38:50.825 --> 00:38:53.040 align:middle line:84%
where are the ones
who are the grounded,

00:38:53.040 --> 00:38:55.800 align:middle line:84%
earthy, they're going to come
in with a tray of cupcakes

00:38:55.800 --> 00:38:56.910 align:middle line:90%
every Friday people.

00:38:56.910 --> 00:38:58.970 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Well, that's
a very different part

00:38:58.970 --> 00:39:00.740 align:middle line:90%
of the body of information.

00:39:00.740 --> 00:39:02.705 align:middle line:84%
This body of
information is vast.

00:39:02.705 --> 00:39:03.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it is.

00:39:03.580 --> 00:39:04.900 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: I know this
show's only an hour,

00:39:04.900 --> 00:39:06.720 align:middle line:84%
but we could talk for
a long time about it.

00:39:06.720 --> 00:39:07.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:39:07.520 --> 00:39:11.280 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: You-- there
is also a consideration

00:39:11.280 --> 00:39:18.070 align:middle line:84%
in your chart about where your
principles exist in your chart.

00:39:18.070 --> 00:39:23.000 align:middle line:84%
There are four quadrants in
a circle, in a circle chart.

00:39:23.000 --> 00:39:25.260 align:middle line:84%
The first quadrant
is what we call

00:39:25.260 --> 00:39:26.890 align:middle line:90%
the psychological quadrant.

00:39:26.890 --> 00:39:28.620 align:middle line:84%
So if you have a
lot of influence,

00:39:28.620 --> 00:39:32.220 align:middle line:84%
a lot of your principles are
located in that first quadrant.

00:39:32.220 --> 00:39:35.330 align:middle line:84%
Then, your job in the world--
part of your job in the world

00:39:35.330 --> 00:39:43.040 align:middle line:84%
is sanity, maintaining a
healthy psychological beingness.

00:39:43.040 --> 00:39:45.940 align:middle line:84%
Second quadrant is the
sociological quadrant.

00:39:45.940 --> 00:39:49.500 align:middle line:84%
If you have a lot of
sociological energies,

00:39:49.500 --> 00:39:51.020 align:middle line:90%
that's where the volunteers are.

00:39:51.020 --> 00:39:52.780 align:middle line:84%
That's where the
politicians are.

00:39:52.780 --> 00:39:54.470 align:middle line:90%
That's where the actors are.

00:39:54.470 --> 00:39:58.250 align:middle line:84%
That's where the
people who are really

00:39:58.250 --> 00:40:01.280 align:middle line:90%
invested in healthy societies.

00:40:01.280 --> 00:40:02.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:40:02.610 --> 00:40:06.460 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Third quadrant is
the quadrant of philosophy,

00:40:06.460 --> 00:40:08.470 align:middle line:90%
the philosophical quadrant.

00:40:08.470 --> 00:40:12.440 align:middle line:84%
So if you have a lot
of, uh, principles

00:40:12.440 --> 00:40:14.460 align:middle line:84%
in the philosophical
quadrant, you

00:40:14.460 --> 00:40:16.800 align:middle line:84%
are basically a
thinker, a philosopher,

00:40:16.800 --> 00:40:20.035 align:middle line:84%
someone who asks
the right questions.

00:40:20.035 --> 00:40:22.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And do I have a
lot of stuff in that one?

00:40:22.160 --> 00:40:22.680 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, you do.

00:40:22.680 --> 00:40:23.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, I bet.

00:40:23.210 --> 00:40:24.230 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, you do.

00:40:24.230 --> 00:40:27.020 align:middle line:84%
That's why we said the
other day on the phone,

00:40:27.020 --> 00:40:29.370 align:middle line:84%
I said, asking the
right questions

00:40:29.370 --> 00:40:31.670 align:middle line:84%
in the right way with
the right vocabulary

00:40:31.670 --> 00:40:33.780 align:middle line:90%
is what gets the right answers.

00:40:33.780 --> 00:40:37.300 align:middle line:84%
That's why you ask
questions, because you know

00:40:37.300 --> 00:40:40.280 align:middle line:90%
how to bring answers forth.

00:40:40.280 --> 00:40:44.280 align:middle line:84%
It's back to what I was saying
earlier about your principles.

00:40:44.280 --> 00:40:46.870 align:middle line:84%
You don't ever ask
yourself, how do I use

00:40:46.870 --> 00:40:49.550 align:middle line:90%
my principle of intelligence.

00:40:49.550 --> 00:40:52.310 align:middle line:84%
The right question is how
do I get out of the way

00:40:52.310 --> 00:40:56.700 align:middle line:84%
so that intelligence can express
in this circumstance, right.

00:40:56.700 --> 00:41:00.360 align:middle line:84%
It's the same question, but
if it's asked correctly,

00:41:00.360 --> 00:41:01.500 align:middle line:90%
the answer is right there.

00:41:01.500 --> 00:41:02.439 align:middle line:90%
You just do it.

00:41:02.439 --> 00:41:03.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You just do it.

00:41:03.480 --> 00:41:03.960 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: You just sit back.

00:41:03.960 --> 00:41:04.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, so--

00:41:04.500 --> 00:41:05.450 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: And do it.

00:41:05.450 --> 00:41:06.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What's
the fourth quadrant?

00:41:06.620 --> 00:41:07.980 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: The
spiritual quadrant.

00:41:07.980 --> 00:41:08.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:41:08.780 --> 00:41:10.830 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: So people who
are heavily, you know,

00:41:10.830 --> 00:41:14.000 align:middle line:84%
invested in the
spiritual quadrant are

00:41:14.000 --> 00:41:18.340 align:middle line:84%
spiritual practitioners and
need to be given the freedom

00:41:18.340 --> 00:41:20.990 align:middle line:90%
to be spiritual practitioners.

00:41:20.990 --> 00:41:23.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk
about some of the words

00:41:23.040 --> 00:41:24.960 align:middle line:84%
in the ascending,
the containment,

00:41:24.960 --> 00:41:29.420 align:middle line:84%
and descending, because this
is-- in ancient traditions,

00:41:29.420 --> 00:41:32.610 align:middle line:84%
as well, the power of
words is really important.

00:41:32.610 --> 00:41:35.140 align:middle line:84%
And we have completely
run roughshod over it.

00:41:35.140 --> 00:41:38.360 align:middle line:84%
I know they add new words
to the Webster's and Oxford

00:41:38.360 --> 00:41:40.440 align:middle line:84%
dictionaries all
the time, that are

00:41:40.440 --> 00:41:45.055 align:middle line:84%
kind of right out of "Brave
New World" and "Animal Farm,"

00:41:45.055 --> 00:41:46.070 align:middle line:90%
Newspeak.

00:41:46.070 --> 00:41:46.870 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah.

00:41:46.870 --> 00:41:48.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Which, that's fine.

00:41:48.080 --> 00:41:49.860 align:middle line:84%
It's just a new
means of expression,

00:41:49.860 --> 00:41:51.620 align:middle line:90%
and language should evolve.

00:41:51.620 --> 00:41:55.070 align:middle line:84%
But there are
classical words that

00:41:55.070 --> 00:41:59.040 align:middle line:84%
have power, substance,
and beauty that are seldom

00:41:59.040 --> 00:42:00.870 align:middle line:90%
used in our vocabulary anymore.

00:42:00.870 --> 00:42:03.580 align:middle line:84%
And I-- Now, I would
skew a little bit

00:42:03.580 --> 00:42:06.580 align:middle line:84%
toward the conspiratorial end
on that and say, interesting,

00:42:06.580 --> 00:42:09.250 align:middle line:84%
these words aren't the words
that are dominant any longer.

00:42:09.250 --> 00:42:12.300 align:middle line:84%
Yet while in ancient
times, for example,

00:42:12.300 --> 00:42:16.550 align:middle line:84%
in ancient Grecian times
when philosophy ruled,

00:42:16.550 --> 00:42:20.290 align:middle line:84%
these words were prominent
in the vocabulary.

00:42:20.290 --> 00:42:21.999 align:middle line:84%
Something's been lost
that's significant.

00:42:21.999 --> 00:42:22.798 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Right.

00:42:22.798 --> 00:42:25.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And your system
has brought them back.

00:42:25.170 --> 00:42:27.660 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, these--
all of the words

00:42:27.660 --> 00:42:32.010 align:middle line:84%
have very specific definitions,
which are slightly different.

00:42:32.010 --> 00:42:34.660 align:middle line:84%
For example, one
of the principles

00:42:34.660 --> 00:42:40.780 align:middle line:84%
that it's the ascending category
is the principle of generosity.

00:42:40.780 --> 00:42:43.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which, the earth
itself, that makes sense.

00:42:43.150 --> 00:42:43.950 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Exactly.

00:42:43.950 --> 00:42:47.080 align:middle line:84%
Now, the principle
of generosity doesn't

00:42:47.080 --> 00:42:49.790 align:middle line:84%
mean you should run around
giving people stuff.

00:42:49.790 --> 00:42:54.920 align:middle line:84%
If you have the principle of
generosity in your garment,

00:42:54.920 --> 00:43:02.470 align:middle line:84%
the imperative of generosity
is the correct balance

00:43:02.470 --> 00:43:05.060 align:middle line:90%
between giving and receiving.

00:43:05.060 --> 00:43:06.640 align:middle line:90%
That's the imperative.

00:43:06.640 --> 00:43:11.920 align:middle line:84%
So people who are
generous, but don't

00:43:11.920 --> 00:43:16.190 align:middle line:84%
allow themselves to receive,
are not really generous.

00:43:16.190 --> 00:43:19.070 align:middle line:90%
They're just buying.

00:43:19.070 --> 00:43:22.290 align:middle line:84%
You know, they're
buying your friendship.

00:43:22.290 --> 00:43:23.260 align:middle line:90%
They're buying favors.

00:43:23.260 --> 00:43:24.854 align:middle line:84%
They're buying
attention or whatever.

00:43:24.854 --> 00:43:27.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, there's
usually some kind of factor,

00:43:27.020 --> 00:43:29.970 align:middle line:84%
subconscious factor under there
that's causing that depletion.

00:43:29.970 --> 00:43:32.030 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Right, so
that's one of the things

00:43:32.030 --> 00:43:37.650 align:middle line:84%
that I say to people who have
generosity in their contract

00:43:37.650 --> 00:43:39.940 align:middle line:90%
or in their pattern.

00:43:39.940 --> 00:43:43.170 align:middle line:90%
Do you get as much as you give?

00:43:43.170 --> 00:43:45.550 align:middle line:90%
And almost everybody says no.

00:43:45.550 --> 00:43:49.650 align:middle line:84%
And I say, OK, is that
a perception problem

00:43:49.650 --> 00:43:51.990 align:middle line:90%
or is that a real problem.

00:43:51.990 --> 00:43:54.060 align:middle line:84%
If it's a perception
problem, it's

00:43:54.060 --> 00:43:57.754 align:middle line:84%
because you think
you always the one

00:43:57.754 --> 00:43:59.920 align:middle line:84%
that's always taking care
of everybody and whatever.

00:43:59.920 --> 00:44:03.550 align:middle line:90%
If it's a real problem, why?

00:44:03.550 --> 00:44:06.550 align:middle line:84%
Why are you not
allowing generosity

00:44:06.550 --> 00:44:08.830 align:middle line:90%
to tell you when to express?

00:44:08.830 --> 00:44:12.040 align:middle line:84%
Why are you willfully
doling out whatever it is,

00:44:12.040 --> 00:44:14.610 align:middle line:84%
energy, time, money,
whatever, you know.

00:44:14.610 --> 00:44:16.770 align:middle line:84%
So that's what
I'm talking about.

00:44:16.770 --> 00:44:19.020 align:middle line:84%
It's not the soul
that needed to learn

00:44:19.020 --> 00:44:20.750 align:middle line:90%
the definition of generosity.

00:44:20.750 --> 00:44:23.590 align:middle line:84%
It's the personality that
needs to get out of the way

00:44:23.590 --> 00:44:25.681 align:middle line:84%
and let generosity
express through.

00:44:25.681 --> 00:44:27.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because that
shows up oftentimes

00:44:27.430 --> 00:44:29.817 align:middle line:84%
as sort of a super
slave syndrome.

00:44:29.817 --> 00:44:31.400 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, yes,
well, now, there's

00:44:31.400 --> 00:44:37.630 align:middle line:84%
another principle that is in
the containing definition that

00:44:37.630 --> 00:44:39.590 align:middle line:90%
is called service.

00:44:39.590 --> 00:44:42.420 align:middle line:84%
And I really get that
a lot with women who

00:44:42.420 --> 00:44:46.350 align:middle line:90%
have service in their patterns.

00:44:46.350 --> 00:44:49.610 align:middle line:84%
They're like, oh, no, I don't
want to be a servant anymore.

00:44:49.610 --> 00:44:51.630 align:middle line:90%
That's all I do is be a servant.

00:44:51.630 --> 00:44:56.920 align:middle line:84%
No, no, no, no, no, service
is not about being a doormat.

00:44:56.920 --> 00:45:02.310 align:middle line:84%
It's about recognizing
that life is a gift.

00:45:02.310 --> 00:45:05.590 align:middle line:84%
And that you are
the gift to life.

00:45:05.590 --> 00:45:08.400 align:middle line:84%
So you're not
serving other people.

00:45:08.400 --> 00:45:11.870 align:middle line:84%
You're serving life
by being alive.

00:45:11.870 --> 00:45:15.140 align:middle line:84%
It's really a very
high principle.

00:45:15.140 --> 00:45:20.800 align:middle line:84%
But, yes, because of
the way we use the word,

00:45:20.800 --> 00:45:23.470 align:middle line:84%
it does turn out to
sometimes scare people,

00:45:23.470 --> 00:45:26.406 align:middle line:84%
meaning that they think
that what I'm saying

00:45:26.406 --> 00:45:28.030 align:middle line:84%
is they are supposed
to run around just

00:45:28.030 --> 00:45:28.354 align:middle line:90%
taking care of people.

00:45:28.354 --> 00:45:29.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Living a
life of servitude.

00:45:29.200 --> 00:45:29.940 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah.

00:45:29.940 --> 00:45:30.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:45:30.470 --> 00:45:31.270 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Exactly.

00:45:31.270 --> 00:45:33.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So I mean,
again, that's what I really

00:45:33.400 --> 00:45:36.790 align:middle line:84%
like about this is the
very specific way in which

00:45:36.790 --> 00:45:40.120 align:middle line:90%
these words are presented.

00:45:40.120 --> 00:45:41.770 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
a couple more words

00:45:41.770 --> 00:45:43.750 align:middle line:84%
in the ascending
patterns that are common.

00:45:43.750 --> 00:45:45.520 align:middle line:84%
And then, I want
to talk about what

00:45:45.520 --> 00:45:47.790 align:middle line:84%
happens in various
cultures, if you read people

00:45:47.790 --> 00:45:48.800 align:middle line:90%
from different cultures.

00:45:48.800 --> 00:45:51.950 align:middle line:84%
But first, a few ascending
words, a few containing words,

00:45:51.950 --> 00:45:53.134 align:middle line:90%
a few descending words.

00:45:53.134 --> 00:45:54.800 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: OK, one of
the ascending words

00:45:54.800 --> 00:45:57.530 align:middle line:84%
that scares people
to death is memory,

00:45:57.530 --> 00:45:59.520 align:middle line:90%
the principle of memory.

00:45:59.520 --> 00:46:03.040 align:middle line:84%
I can't tell you how many times,
when I say to someone, OK,

00:46:03.040 --> 00:46:04.900 align:middle line:84%
one of your main
principles is memory.

00:46:04.900 --> 00:46:06.277 align:middle line:84%
Oh, no, I have a
terrible memory.

00:46:06.277 --> 00:46:07.360 align:middle line:90%
I can't remember anything.

00:46:07.360 --> 00:46:08.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, oh, oh.

00:46:08.400 --> 00:46:09.740 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Oh, no, I'm
really bad at memory.

00:46:09.740 --> 00:46:10.540 align:middle line:90%
This is terrible.

00:46:10.540 --> 00:46:12.406 align:middle line:90%
I'm a failure at my own--

00:46:12.406 --> 00:46:13.206 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Garment.

00:46:13.206 --> 00:46:14.830 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Beingness, yeah.

00:46:14.830 --> 00:46:19.220 align:middle line:84%
No, no, no, no, no,
memory is that moment

00:46:19.220 --> 00:46:24.240 align:middle line:84%
in the development
of the universe where

00:46:24.240 --> 00:46:29.020 align:middle line:84%
a cell remembered how to
recreate itself exactly.

00:46:29.020 --> 00:46:31.979 align:middle line:84%
That level of memory
is beyond anything

00:46:31.979 --> 00:46:33.270 align:middle line:90%
that goes on in the head brain.

00:46:33.270 --> 00:46:35.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's an
inherent kind of memory.

00:46:35.020 --> 00:46:37.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, it's
a very, very deep

00:46:37.200 --> 00:46:42.130 align:middle line:84%
and profound level of
consciousness about what life

00:46:42.130 --> 00:46:46.440 align:middle line:84%
is, about how life knows how
to reconstruct and reproduce

00:46:46.440 --> 00:46:48.020 align:middle line:90%
itself.

00:46:48.020 --> 00:46:55.842 align:middle line:84%
Memory, the principle, is
focused in the mineral kingdom.

00:46:55.842 --> 00:46:58.300 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I was going to say,
an ascending principle coming

00:46:58.300 --> 00:46:59.170 align:middle line:90%
from the earth.

00:46:59.170 --> 00:47:01.086 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: It's focused
in the mineral kingdom.

00:47:01.086 --> 00:47:03.830 align:middle line:84%
In your body, it's
focused in the bones.

00:47:03.830 --> 00:47:07.510 align:middle line:84%
When anthropologists
find a bone,

00:47:07.510 --> 00:47:09.370 align:middle line:84%
they are very, very
excited because they

00:47:09.370 --> 00:47:13.670 align:middle line:84%
can tell a lot about
that being's lifetime.

00:47:13.670 --> 00:47:14.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:47:14.470 --> 00:47:15.886 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: By just
one little piece

00:47:15.886 --> 00:47:17.860 align:middle line:84%
of a bone because all
of that information

00:47:17.860 --> 00:47:21.620 align:middle line:84%
was downloaded into the bones,
just like the earth downloads

00:47:21.620 --> 00:47:23.410 align:middle line:90%
her information into the stones.

00:47:23.410 --> 00:47:25.692 align:middle line:90%
So memory is another one.

00:47:25.692 --> 00:47:27.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: More kind
of DNA-related.

00:47:27.150 --> 00:47:28.030 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, yes.

00:47:28.030 --> 00:47:31.422 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, and another one.

00:47:31.422 --> 00:47:32.880 align:middle line:84%
Because we can't
go through all 30,

00:47:32.880 --> 00:47:34.671 align:middle line:84%
we wouldn't have time
to go through all 30.

00:47:34.671 --> 00:47:36.980 align:middle line:84%
But I want to give people a
feeling for the principles

00:47:36.980 --> 00:47:39.860 align:middle line:84%
and why these words are
with each of these three

00:47:39.860 --> 00:47:41.210 align:middle line:90%
groupings of principles.

00:47:41.210 --> 00:47:42.190 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Right.

00:47:42.190 --> 00:47:44.180 align:middle line:84%
There's another
one, purity, it's

00:47:44.180 --> 00:47:47.080 align:middle line:90%
another ascending principle.

00:47:47.080 --> 00:47:51.500 align:middle line:84%
Now, purity to some
people means, you know--

00:47:51.500 --> 00:47:52.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Chastity.

00:47:52.300 --> 00:47:52.750 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Chastity.

00:47:52.750 --> 00:47:53.708 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Or something.

00:47:53.708 --> 00:47:56.185 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Right, just like
it, being really nice.

00:47:56.185 --> 00:47:58.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:47:58.170 --> 00:48:00.680 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Purity, as
a spiritual principle,

00:48:00.680 --> 00:48:07.180 align:middle line:84%
has to do with being able to
recognize original intention.

00:48:07.180 --> 00:48:11.360 align:middle line:84%
So when I say to
somebody, you have purity,

00:48:11.360 --> 00:48:14.830 align:middle line:84%
I will often say to them,
when you look at a rose,

00:48:14.830 --> 00:48:16.820 align:middle line:90%
you're looking at a flower.

00:48:16.820 --> 00:48:19.100 align:middle line:84%
But you're also
looking at roseness.

00:48:19.100 --> 00:48:22.640 align:middle line:84%
You're also looking
at flowerness.

00:48:22.640 --> 00:48:25.510 align:middle line:84%
You're also looking
at plantness.

00:48:25.510 --> 00:48:28.410 align:middle line:90%
You're also looking at seedness.

00:48:28.410 --> 00:48:30.810 align:middle line:84%
You know, you can
see all the way back

00:48:30.810 --> 00:48:36.350 align:middle line:84%
to the original intention,
the seed idea of something.

00:48:36.350 --> 00:48:41.450 align:middle line:84%
So when someone is, who has
purity, is in your presence,

00:48:41.450 --> 00:48:44.170 align:middle line:84%
they can overlook all
of the flaws that have

00:48:44.170 --> 00:48:45.505 align:middle line:90%
happened between original idea.

00:48:45.505 --> 00:48:47.380 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And see the
essence of who you are.

00:48:47.380 --> 00:48:48.760 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: And see
the essence of it.

00:48:48.760 --> 00:48:49.040 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:48:49.040 --> 00:48:50.255 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Whether
it's who you are--

00:48:50.255 --> 00:48:51.065 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Or what it is.

00:48:51.065 --> 00:48:52.156 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: The idea or whatever.

00:48:52.156 --> 00:48:53.072 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The essence.

00:48:53.072 --> 00:48:55.594 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: And these
people help clarify.

00:48:55.594 --> 00:48:56.885 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, that's beautiful.

00:48:56.885 --> 00:48:59.560 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: They're like the
liver of an organization, right.

00:48:59.560 --> 00:49:02.750 align:middle line:84%
They help clarify and take it
back to the original intent.

00:49:02.750 --> 00:49:02.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's beautiful.

00:49:02.960 --> 00:49:04.760 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: So those are
three ascending principles.

00:49:04.760 --> 00:49:06.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Where's innocence?

00:49:06.060 --> 00:49:07.770 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Innocence is also
an ascending principle.

00:49:07.770 --> 00:49:10.061 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's what I was
wondering because sometimes

00:49:10.061 --> 00:49:12.280 align:middle line:84%
that's a-- people in our
common vernacular align

00:49:12.280 --> 00:49:13.080 align:middle line:90%
that with purity.

00:49:13.080 --> 00:49:14.920 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, and
innocence and purity

00:49:14.920 --> 00:49:17.560 align:middle line:84%
sit right next to
each other on this.

00:49:17.560 --> 00:49:21.660 align:middle line:84%
But innocence, now, as
a spiritual principle

00:49:21.660 --> 00:49:27.230 align:middle line:84%
is the ability to be taught,
teachability, teachingness.

00:49:27.230 --> 00:49:29.440 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's like
you can always--

00:49:29.440 --> 00:49:33.440 align:middle line:84%
like a child plays
with a toy and then

00:49:33.440 --> 00:49:35.040 align:middle line:84%
you hide the toy
behind your back,

00:49:35.040 --> 00:49:38.059 align:middle line:84%
and the child thinks the toy
has completely disappeared.

00:49:38.059 --> 00:49:39.600 align:middle line:84%
And then, you bring
the toy back out,

00:49:39.600 --> 00:49:42.260 align:middle line:84%
and it's like he's never
seen the toy before, right.

00:49:42.260 --> 00:49:45.830 align:middle line:84%
Well, innocence-- people
with innocence in their chart

00:49:45.830 --> 00:49:50.410 align:middle line:84%
somewhere have that ability
to greet every circumstance

00:49:50.410 --> 00:49:52.470 align:middle line:84%
as if they'd never
been there before.

00:49:52.470 --> 00:49:53.990 align:middle line:84%
They don't live
in the been there,

00:49:53.990 --> 00:49:58.870 align:middle line:84%
done that kind of cynicism
that I live in so--

00:49:58.870 --> 00:50:00.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I live more like that.

00:50:00.340 --> 00:50:01.214 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah, yeah.

00:50:01.214 --> 00:50:02.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, like it's new.

00:50:02.820 --> 00:50:06.720 align:middle line:84%
The downside of that is, if
something doesn't feel good,

00:50:06.720 --> 00:50:07.592 align:middle line:90%
that's it.

00:50:07.592 --> 00:50:08.482 align:middle line:90%
That's life now.

00:50:08.482 --> 00:50:09.690 align:middle line:90%
That's going to last forever.

00:50:09.690 --> 00:50:11.380 align:middle line:84%
When it's going to
pass by the next day.

00:50:11.380 --> 00:50:12.180 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Right.

00:50:12.180 --> 00:50:13.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And the same
thing if it's good.

00:50:13.930 --> 00:50:15.960 align:middle line:84%
So maybe I've got that
somewhere in there.

00:50:15.960 --> 00:50:16.760 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:50:16.760 --> 00:50:18.420 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Somewhere,
probably you do.

00:50:18.420 --> 00:50:19.370 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Anyway, so go ahead.

00:50:19.370 --> 00:50:19.850 align:middle line:90%
So that's--

00:50:19.850 --> 00:50:20.140 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: All right.

00:50:20.140 --> 00:50:22.540 align:middle line:84%
So a couple-- let's see,
a couple of the containing

00:50:22.540 --> 00:50:23.550 align:middle line:90%
principles.

00:50:23.550 --> 00:50:27.570 align:middle line:84%
Well, one of them
is reciprocity.

00:50:27.570 --> 00:50:32.710 align:middle line:84%
So reciprocity is a
little bit like generosity

00:50:32.710 --> 00:50:37.360 align:middle line:84%
in that it has to do with that
kind of infinity sign, you

00:50:37.360 --> 00:50:40.420 align:middle line:84%
know, what comes
around goes around.

00:50:40.420 --> 00:50:43.659 align:middle line:84%
So without getting into the
blame the victim mentality,

00:50:43.659 --> 00:50:45.450 align:middle line:84%
you know, if something
bad happened to you,

00:50:45.450 --> 00:50:46.470 align:middle line:90%
it's because you deserve it.

00:50:46.470 --> 00:50:46.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:50:46.700 --> 00:50:48.533 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: That's not
what I'm talking about.

00:50:48.533 --> 00:50:52.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm just talking about the whole
idea of kind of pay it forward

00:50:52.310 --> 00:50:54.580 align:middle line:90%
and then it comes back to you.

00:50:54.580 --> 00:50:57.970 align:middle line:84%
And you can watch that
often more clearly

00:50:57.970 --> 00:51:00.990 align:middle line:84%
outside of yourself
than in yourself

00:51:00.990 --> 00:51:03.720 align:middle line:84%
because when you're watching
reciprocity inside yourself,

00:51:03.720 --> 00:51:07.100 align:middle line:84%
you tend to get blame me
and guilty, and you know,

00:51:07.100 --> 00:51:07.900 align:middle line:90%
I did something.

00:51:07.900 --> 00:51:10.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But this is more
to understand, like you say,

00:51:10.400 --> 00:51:13.200 align:middle line:84%
that infinite flow of energy
in life, back and forth.

00:51:13.200 --> 00:51:14.000 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, yes.

00:51:14.000 --> 00:51:15.958 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What goes out,
eventually comes back.

00:51:15.958 --> 00:51:20.070 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, and so you have
kind of that witness ability

00:51:20.070 --> 00:51:23.840 align:middle line:84%
to watch how that-- how
that works and go, huh, wow,

00:51:23.840 --> 00:51:25.200 align:middle line:90%
that's cool, right.

00:51:25.200 --> 00:51:27.365 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:51:27.365 --> 00:51:29.740 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Let's see, what's
another containing principle?

00:51:29.740 --> 00:51:33.470 align:middle line:84%
Well, intelligence is one of
the containing principles.

00:51:33.470 --> 00:51:37.780 align:middle line:84%
So again, most people
will say, you know--

00:51:37.780 --> 00:51:38.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: IQ.

00:51:38.580 --> 00:51:40.871 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah, it's about
your-- it's about your brain

00:51:40.871 --> 00:51:41.770 align:middle line:90%
smarts.

00:51:41.770 --> 00:51:43.570 align:middle line:84%
But the principle
of intelligence

00:51:43.570 --> 00:51:47.010 align:middle line:84%
is really about
sharing information.

00:51:47.010 --> 00:51:50.000 align:middle line:84%
It's about the distribution
of information.

00:51:50.000 --> 00:51:54.300 align:middle line:84%
It's like the central nervous
system of the cosmic body.

00:51:54.300 --> 00:51:58.510 align:middle line:84%
So intelligence takes in
information without judging it

00:51:58.510 --> 00:52:00.960 align:middle line:90%
and shares it freely.

00:52:00.960 --> 00:52:04.310 align:middle line:84%
Now, here's something
that's really interesting.

00:52:04.310 --> 00:52:09.250 align:middle line:84%
If you-- if you give the
United States of America, July

00:52:09.250 --> 00:52:12.960 align:middle line:84%
the 4th, 1776,
birthday, the sun,

00:52:12.960 --> 00:52:15.770 align:middle line:84%
the primary principle of
the United States of America

00:52:15.770 --> 00:52:20.920 align:middle line:84%
is intelligence, the
free flow of information.

00:52:20.920 --> 00:52:24.350 align:middle line:84%
And that's what almost
anybody who ever comes here

00:52:24.350 --> 00:52:26.950 align:middle line:90%
from another country will say.

00:52:26.950 --> 00:52:28.660 align:middle line:84%
There's so much
information here.

00:52:28.660 --> 00:52:31.122 align:middle line:90%
You can find out everything.

00:52:31.122 --> 00:52:32.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, that's true.

00:52:32.330 --> 00:52:35.120 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: And we're in
such an interesting time

00:52:35.120 --> 00:52:40.710 align:middle line:84%
right now where we're looking
at free flow of information.

00:52:40.710 --> 00:52:43.150 align:middle line:84%
We're looking at, should
we know everything

00:52:43.150 --> 00:52:45.040 align:middle line:84%
that the government
is doing and saying.

00:52:45.040 --> 00:52:47.970 align:middle line:84%
And should we know
all of these secrets?

00:52:47.970 --> 00:52:50.350 align:middle line:90%
Is that our right?

00:52:50.350 --> 00:52:52.290 align:middle line:90%
Because that is our birthmark.

00:52:52.290 --> 00:52:56.610 align:middle line:84%
Or you know, and the difference
between the free flow

00:52:56.610 --> 00:52:59.010 align:middle line:84%
of information and
security in your own home.

00:52:59.010 --> 00:53:01.200 align:middle line:84%
And I mean, the
country is actually

00:53:01.200 --> 00:53:02.659 align:middle line:84%
having that
conversation right now.

00:53:02.659 --> 00:53:03.533 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it is.

00:53:03.533 --> 00:53:06.000 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: As if we're-- as
if we're in some kind of real

00:53:06.000 --> 00:53:09.090 align:middle line:90%
interesting rebirth process.

00:53:09.090 --> 00:53:10.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Very interesting.

00:53:10.470 --> 00:53:13.950 align:middle line:84%
OK, so let's talk about some of
the descending principles now.

00:53:13.950 --> 00:53:15.070 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: All right.

00:53:15.070 --> 00:53:15.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Words.

00:53:15.870 --> 00:53:19.860 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: There's a descending
principle called randomness,

00:53:19.860 --> 00:53:22.800 align:middle line:84%
scares the bejesus out
of people because it

00:53:22.800 --> 00:53:29.800 align:middle line:84%
seems so wacky to say, oh,
look, your primary principle is

00:53:29.800 --> 00:53:30.900 align:middle line:90%
randomness.

00:53:30.900 --> 00:53:32.136 align:middle line:90%
Oh, no, no, no.

00:53:32.136 --> 00:53:33.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, I
have no bearings.

00:53:33.510 --> 00:53:34.030 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, yes.

00:53:34.030 --> 00:53:34.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:53:34.960 --> 00:53:37.080 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: But as a
spiritual principle,

00:53:37.080 --> 00:53:43.670 align:middle line:84%
it's defined as that ability
to consider all possibilities

00:53:43.670 --> 00:53:48.790 align:middle line:84%
and then allow the one that
needs to be expressed freedom

00:53:48.790 --> 00:53:50.010 align:middle line:90%
to come forward.

00:53:50.010 --> 00:53:54.287 align:middle line:84%
So the analogy I use
is like a kaleidoscope.

00:53:54.287 --> 00:53:55.870 align:middle line:84%
You're looking through
a kaleidoscope.

00:53:55.870 --> 00:53:56.920 align:middle line:90%
You see a pattern.

00:53:56.920 --> 00:53:57.720 align:middle line:90%
You twist it.

00:53:57.720 --> 00:54:00.300 align:middle line:84%
All of those rocks go
chinka chinka chinka.

00:54:00.300 --> 00:54:03.540 align:middle line:84%
You know it's all
the same rocks.

00:54:03.540 --> 00:54:04.940 align:middle line:90%
It strikes another pattern.

00:54:04.940 --> 00:54:06.681 align:middle line:84%
It can't possibly be
all the same rocks

00:54:06.681 --> 00:54:08.180 align:middle line:84%
because the pattern
is so different.

00:54:08.180 --> 00:54:08.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:54:08.980 --> 00:54:11.430 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: But that
chinka chinka chinka part

00:54:11.430 --> 00:54:13.955 align:middle line:84%
is where you live
if randomness is

00:54:13.955 --> 00:54:17.515 align:middle line:84%
part of your-- part
of your practice, part

00:54:17.515 --> 00:54:19.550 align:middle line:90%
of your influence.

00:54:19.550 --> 00:54:23.970 align:middle line:84%
And so you have to learn how
to-- you can't be a control

00:54:23.970 --> 00:54:25.977 align:middle line:84%
freak if randomness
is a part of your--

00:54:25.977 --> 00:54:27.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, interesting.

00:54:27.060 --> 00:54:28.185 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: --of your system.

00:54:28.185 --> 00:54:33.044 align:middle line:84%
You have to be willing for all
possibilities to come through.

00:54:33.044 --> 00:54:34.460 align:middle line:84%
And I'll give you
a quick example.

00:54:34.460 --> 00:54:39.790 align:middle line:84%
A friend of mine's daughter, I
think it's her son's principle,

00:54:39.790 --> 00:54:42.000 align:middle line:90%
randomness.

00:54:42.000 --> 00:54:47.420 align:middle line:84%
Well, she had a heck of a
time deciding what college she

00:54:47.420 --> 00:54:49.320 align:middle line:90%
wanted to go to.

00:54:49.320 --> 00:54:52.550 align:middle line:84%
She-- or even what college
she wanted to apply to.

00:54:52.550 --> 00:54:54.460 align:middle line:84%
And she needed to
see all of them.

00:54:54.460 --> 00:54:56.760 align:middle line:84%
And it was one of those--
they live in California,

00:54:56.760 --> 00:54:58.320 align:middle line:84%
and now, they've
got to go to Boston.

00:54:58.320 --> 00:55:00.486 align:middle line:84%
And now, they've got to go,
you know-- it was, like,

00:55:00.486 --> 00:55:04.380 align:middle line:84%
expensive and crazy-making,
because she could not

00:55:04.380 --> 00:55:05.940 align:middle line:90%
make a choice.

00:55:05.940 --> 00:55:10.130 align:middle line:84%
But the mother knew
her principles.

00:55:10.130 --> 00:55:12.880 align:middle line:84%
And the mother knew
randomness was her principle.

00:55:12.880 --> 00:55:14.860 align:middle line:84%
And this is the
way it had to be.

00:55:14.860 --> 00:55:16.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So she had to see
it all, considerate it all

00:55:16.120 --> 00:55:17.030 align:middle line:90%
and let it shake down.

00:55:17.030 --> 00:55:17.830 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Right.

00:55:17.830 --> 00:55:20.470 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you didn't know
that about your child,

00:55:20.470 --> 00:55:22.310 align:middle line:90%
you might get frustrated and--

00:55:22.310 --> 00:55:24.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or just say,
no, we're not doing that.

00:55:24.310 --> 00:55:24.760 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah.

00:55:24.760 --> 00:55:25.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:55:25.000 --> 00:55:26.160 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Yeah,
make up your mind.

00:55:26.160 --> 00:55:26.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:55:26.960 --> 00:55:29.610 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: So this is one of
the advantages of knowing

00:55:29.610 --> 00:55:30.940 align:middle line:90%
your children's principles--

00:55:30.940 --> 00:55:31.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:55:31.190 --> 00:55:33.600 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: --is being able to
create an environment that

00:55:33.600 --> 00:55:36.660 align:middle line:90%
allows them to express.

00:55:36.660 --> 00:55:42.370 align:middle line:84%
Because, you know, it
is parental structures

00:55:42.370 --> 00:55:45.270 align:middle line:84%
that make us block a lot
of our authentic selves.

00:55:45.270 --> 00:55:46.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:55:46.420 --> 00:55:48.255 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: All right,
so that's randomness.

00:55:48.255 --> 00:55:50.260 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We already
talked about dreaming so--

00:55:50.260 --> 00:55:52.051 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: We already
talked about dreaming.

00:55:52.051 --> 00:55:56.500 align:middle line:84%
So another one is desire,
the principle of desire.

00:55:56.500 --> 00:56:01.420 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you have
desire in your pattern,

00:56:01.420 --> 00:56:05.070 align:middle line:84%
and you haven't really
learned how to let it express,

00:56:05.070 --> 00:56:08.940 align:middle line:84%
it's probably going to
show up as acquisitional.

00:56:08.940 --> 00:56:11.110 align:middle line:84%
I like this, and I want
this, and I want that.

00:56:11.110 --> 00:56:13.600 align:middle line:84%
And if I get this, my
life will be better.

00:56:13.600 --> 00:56:15.947 align:middle line:84%
If I get that job, my
life will be better.

00:56:15.947 --> 00:56:18.530 align:middle line:84%
Now, I've got that job so I need
to have these clothes to wear

00:56:18.530 --> 00:56:19.040 align:middle line:90%
to that job.

00:56:19.040 --> 00:56:20.130 align:middle line:84%
And then, my life
will be better.

00:56:20.130 --> 00:56:21.980 align:middle line:84%
And now, I want that
house because then,

00:56:21.980 --> 00:56:23.060 align:middle line:90%
my life will be better.

00:56:23.060 --> 00:56:25.020 align:middle line:84%
And everybody with
an ounce of sense

00:56:25.020 --> 00:56:29.540 align:middle line:84%
knows that there is
no amount of stuff

00:56:29.540 --> 00:56:31.890 align:middle line:84%
you can own that's going
to make your life better.

00:56:31.890 --> 00:56:32.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:56:32.190 --> 00:56:32.300 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: It's not.

00:56:32.300 --> 00:56:34.920 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But that does
afflict people, maybe more that

00:56:34.920 --> 00:56:37.010 align:middle line:84%
have a guiding
principle of desire

00:56:37.010 --> 00:56:38.987 align:middle line:84%
in their chart in
the sun, right.

00:56:38.987 --> 00:56:40.070 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: Yes, until you--

00:56:40.070 --> 00:56:40.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: If it's--

00:56:40.410 --> 00:56:41.826 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Until,
until you finally

00:56:41.826 --> 00:56:47.500 align:middle line:84%
realize that that longing
is longing for the soul,

00:56:47.500 --> 00:56:49.840 align:middle line:84%
is longing for that deep
connection with the soul.

00:56:49.840 --> 00:56:51.810 align:middle line:90%
It's a longing to go home.

00:56:51.810 --> 00:56:54.280 align:middle line:84%
That's what makes
your life better.

00:56:54.280 --> 00:57:01.575 align:middle line:84%
So when desire really matures
and manifests through someone,

00:57:01.575 --> 00:57:03.162 align:middle line:90%
they tend to be minimalists.

00:57:03.162 --> 00:57:04.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Hm mm.

00:57:04.160 --> 00:57:07.251 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Because it's not
about acquisition at all.

00:57:07.251 --> 00:57:08.167 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:57:08.167 --> 00:57:09.480 align:middle line:90%
>>KAPLAN: So, yeah.

00:57:09.480 --> 00:57:11.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now,
let's talk about what

00:57:11.600 --> 00:57:14.050 align:middle line:84%
