from various cultures.

00:57:14.050 --> 00:57:16.420 align:middle line:84%
Do you find culturally
certain words

00:57:16.420 --> 00:57:19.920 align:middle line:84%
might be more dominant
in some countries

00:57:19.920 --> 00:57:23.350 align:middle line:84%
or some cultural
backgrounds than others?

00:57:23.350 --> 00:57:24.650 align:middle line:90%
I'm just curious about that.

00:57:24.650 --> 00:57:26.650 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: You know, that
is kind of a challenge.

00:57:26.650 --> 00:57:29.770 align:middle line:84%
And I haven't worked a lot
with non-Western cultures.

00:57:29.770 --> 00:57:30.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:57:30.570 --> 00:57:34.250 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: You know, so when
I'm speaking with someone from

00:57:34.250 --> 00:57:35.050 align:middle line:90%
Europe--

00:57:35.050 --> 00:57:36.760 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:57:36.760 --> 00:57:40.280 align:middle line:84%
>>KAPLAN: Or even someone
from South America,

00:57:40.280 --> 00:57:43.030 align:middle line:90%
