service thing, you know.

00:58:47.410 --> 00:58:49.340 align:middle line:84%
Most people think of
humility as being,

00:58:49.340 --> 00:58:52.820 align:middle line:90%
like, the doormat syndrome.

00:58:52.820 --> 00:58:54.420 align:middle line:90%
You've got to be quiet.

00:58:54.420 --> 00:58:58.240 align:middle line:84%
You've got to be,
you know-- the way

00:58:58.240 --> 00:59:02.920 align:middle line:84%
the angels defined humility
is they said it is equally as

00:59:02.920 --> 00:59:05.710 align:middle line:84%
arrogant to think too
little of yourself

00:59:05.710 --> 00:59:08.680 align:middle line:84%
as it is to think
too much of yourself.

00:59:08.680 --> 00:59:12.390 align:middle line:84%
So if humility is in
your chart, your job

00:59:12.390 --> 00:59:19.590 align:middle line:84%
is to be authentic-- an
authentic knower of yourself.

00:59:19.590 --> 00:59:22.260 align:middle line:90%
That has been my job.

00:59:22.260 --> 00:59:25.320 align:middle line:84%
That is why I'm not
much of a self-promoter

00:59:25.320 --> 00:59:28.870 align:middle line:84%
because I have to
spend a lot of time

00:59:28.870 --> 00:59:33.390 align:middle line:84%
making sure I'm not
inflated or deflated.

00:59:33.390 --> 00:59:38.160 align:middle line:84%
I am only available
for my principles

00:59:38.160 --> 00:59:41.970 align:middle line:84%
to express through me when I
am in my most authentic knowing

00:59:41.970 --> 00:59:43.710 align:middle line:90%
self.

00:59:43.710 --> 00:59:44.930 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

